Description.val: The Aerial Targets program provides threat representative target capabilities to meet requirements for weapons systems test and evaluation and fleet training. The program is composed of a series of continuing target production programs whose product line includes powered subsonic and supersonic targets, towed targets, and necessary Target Threat Simulation Program (TTSP) and Target Common Avionics Equipment.

Justification.val:
The FY 2016 funding request was reduced by $5.2 million to account for the availability of prior year execution balances.

FY16 funding is required for continued procurement of GQM-163A Supersonic Sea Skimming Targets (SSST),  Target Control and Target Augmentation and Auxiliary Systems including target command/control equipment, scoring equipment, location and identification equipment, navigation equipment, electronic countermeasures equipment and active emitter augmentation equipment. Additionally, FY16 funds will continue funding BQM-34 Subsonic Target configuration modification mitigating the inventory shortfall(s) due to the return of Fleet, live-fire, training. 

The decrease in funding from FY15 to FY16 is due to the reprogramming of BQM-177 Subsonic Aerial Target (SSAT) WPN funds to RDT&E in order to address technical issues in guidance and control, software development, 6 Degrees of Freedom (6DOF) modeling, and complete the Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) program. Milestone (MS) C is scheduled for FY17.

The decrease in funding from FY15 to FY16 is also due to the reprogramming of the GQM-173A Multi-Stage Supersonic Target (MSST) WPN funds to RDT&E in order to mitigate a funding shortfall and continue the Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD)  phase to complete required testing. The MSST program will field a short range rocket-launched, supersonic, vehicle in FY18 as an incremental capability to satisfy the near term Fleet test requirements with an End-to-End capability to follow in later years. Funding will be addressed in future budget cycles.

GQM-163A (SSST) long lead component funds are for the procurement of D6AC steel for production of ducted rocket housings.

Name.@footnote: EM452 BQM Target Modification: Modification of BQM34 continues in FY15 and FY16.

EMA01: GQM-173A (MSST) conducted a technical re-baseline in order to correct deficiencies found during Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD). MSST funding in FY16 was realigned to RDTE to support the re-baselined EMD program.

EM203 GQM-163A (SSST): EM203 funding restored for the procurement of GQM-163A (SSST) in FY16-FY17. This procurement strategy is deemed more cost effective than separate target/high diver kit procurements. Prior Year quantity and cost increased by $4.353M and one additional unit due to FY13 FMS reprogrammed funding (reference FY13-13 Prior Approval Reprogramming Action).  Funds in FY18 realigned from EM031, BQM-177, to support additional GQM-163A target quantities due to an increase in planned Fleet live-fire testing events.

Name.@footnote: EM442 Install/Mission Kits: FY15 is composed of MK-70 Boosters, Augmented Flight Termination System (AFTS) and Mission Specific Equipment (MSE) Kits, and Orbital Front System Kits. FY16 is composed of MK-70 Boosters, AFTS and MSE Kits.
Long lead component funds are required in FY15-FY18 for the procurement of D6AC steel for production of GQM-163A ducted rocket housings.

EM304 ECM/Emitter Equipment (TTSP) increase in FY2018 and beyond is a result of the transition to the procurement phase of the Filthy Buzzard Digital Radio Frequency Memory Modulator (FBZ DRFM).  Completion of the RDTE design/development efforts to baseline the FBZ DRFM occurs in FY15.  This baseline multi-channel FBZ DRFM provides state-of-the art in threat electronic attack and active emitter simulators for test and evaluation of US Navy weapon systems and Operator training.

EM307 Target Common Avionics Equipment was created in PB15 to consolidate existing requirements under Cost Codes EM301, EM302, EM303 and EM305 and includes the following products: System for Naval Target Control (SNTC), Navy Common Datalink (NCDL) and other Common Avionics components.
